<% content_for :title, "Walkthrough — hand it off" %>

<section class="walkthrough">
  <%= render "progress" %>

  <h1>A different person approves it — and it stamps.</h1>

  <p>
    Step into the <b>approver</b>. They did not prepare this run, so for them the
    gate opens: the real <b>Approve</b> button appears below, and pressing it
    stamps the run.
  </p>

  <p class="wt-actions">
    <%= button_to "Act as the approver", act_as_path(id: @approver.id),
          method: :post, class: "button--primary" %>
  </p>

  <%= render @pay_run %>

  <div class="actions-row">
    <%# Renders only when the ambient subject may approve this run — i.e. once
        you are acting as the approver. For anyone else it is (correctly) absent. %>
    <%= render ApproveButtonComponent.new(record: @pay_run) %>
    <%= link_to "View the run", pay_run_path(@pay_run) %>
  </div>

  <p>
    That is the honest path: prepared by one person, approved by another. Now the
    headline — can you get around it by <em>impersonating</em> the approver?
  </p>

  <p class="wt-actions">
    <%= link_to "Next: the headline →", walkthrough_path(step: "either"), class: "button" %>
  </p>
</section>
